ok got it to work.

I run avast among other stuff and this seem relevant.

http://forum.avast.com/index.php?PHPSESSID=soqv3s9ot68och68hf6inqm1a1&topic=116838.30

tried the suggestion to the letter.

read it from the link given...... not sure if this issue is effecting others. hope it helps.

1) Disable self defense
2) Go to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESYSTEMCurrentControlSetservicesAswVmm and change "Start" value to 4
3) Enable self defense
4) Reboot

you may or may not have this registry value.

and to use it you will need proper security permissions...

in regedit.... go to location specified.... right click on its name ( AswVmm ) that name lol...

select permissions. .. user... full control... apply ok then tweak the start entry.... right click it... modify.... should be 0 and change to 4... save blah blah blah.... there ya go.

cheers all.
